What you need to know:  Hours after confirming they had traded superstar James Harden to the Philadelphia 76ers -- dismantling their "Big Three" of Harden, Kyrie Irving and Kevin Durant -- the Nets couldn't hang on to a nine-point third-quarter lead against the Wizards.With Durant still sidelined by a knee injury, Irving scored 31 points with five rebounds and six assists to lead the Nets.